---
import MarketingLayout from '../layouts/MarketingLayout.astro';
import FaqItem from '../components/FaqItem.astro';
---

<MarketingLayout title="FAQ - BOMexplorer" currentPage="faq">
	<section class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<div class="text-center mb-16">
				<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 font-mono">
					Frequently asked questions
				</h1>
				<p class="text-xl text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
					Everything you need to know about BOMexplorer
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="space-y-4" id="faq-accordion">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Getting started</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="What file formats does BOMexplorer accept?"
					answer="BOMexplorer accepts KiCad BOM CSV exports (Symbol Fields Table), Altium BOM exports, and generic CSV formats. Drag-and-drop your file — intelligent column header mapping handles Refs, RefDes, Designator, Qty, MPN, Value, and more automatically."
				/>


				<FaqItem
					question="Which KiCad versions are supported?"
					answer="BOMexplorer works with BOM CSV files from KiCad 5.0 and later. It also supports Altium BOM exports and any generic CSV with recognizable column headers."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How do I get started?"
					answer="Simply upload your BOM CSV file. BOMexplorer auto-detects columns, matches parts against providers, and presents results in seconds. No configuration needed to start."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Providers & matching</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="Which providers are supported?"
					answer="Free tier: OEMSecrets (free aggregator), DigiKey (direct API), and Mouser (direct API). Pro tier adds Nexar (premium — lifecycle status, tech specs) and FindChips (premium aggregator). Free users see premium providers listed in matching results with a 'premium_plan_required' reason."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How does provider fallback work?"
					answer="If the active provider returns no results for a component, BOMexplorer automatically tries the next configured provider in sequence. This continues until a match is found or all providers are exhausted. Admins can configure the provider priority order."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What is a 'confidence score'?"
					answer="Confidence badges indicate match type: Exact MPN (highest confidence), Parametric match, Keyword match, AI-suggested, and Unmatched. Scores help you quickly assess match reliability at a glance."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How does the matching algorithm work?"
					answer="Hierarchical matching: (1) Exact MPN match → (2) Hyphen-stripped MPN match → (3) Distributor part number match → (4) Keyword search. Multi-stage matching maximizes coverage across providers."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">AI features</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="What is AI Assist?"
					answer="AI Assist has two components: (1) Natural language BOM filtering — type plain English queries like 'show me capacitors under $0.10' to highlight matching rows, and (2) AI part classification for components that traditional matching can't handle."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What is AI Explainer?"
					answer="AI Explainer provides AI-powered explanations and insights for component data. Free tier: 5 invocations/month. Pro tier: 20 invocations/month."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How many AI Assist lines do I get?"
					answer="Free tier: 50 AI Assist lines per month. Pro tier: 500 AI Assist lines per month. Both natural language query and AI classification count toward this limit."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Monitoring & alerts</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="How often are parts re-checked?"
					answer="Pro tier: automated overnight re-query via Celery background job. All active BOM lines are re-checked for price and stock changes while you sleep. Free tier: manual refresh available."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What supply chain flags are detected?"
					answer="Out-of-stock, low-stock, price spikes, end-of-life (EOL) notices, and lead-time increases. Each flag has a lifecycle: Open → Watching → Ignored → Resolved with snooze support."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How are alerts delivered?"
					answer="Alerts appear in-app with visual flag indicators. Pro tier also receives morning digest emails summarizing all new flags detected overnight. Configure thresholds per project in preferences."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Can I set custom stock thresholds?"
					answer="Yes, per-project overrides let you set custom stock level thresholds for alerts. Global preferences define default behavior, and projects inherit those values unless overridden."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Substitution & alternatives</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="How do I swap a part?"
					answer="Navigate to the Alternatives page for any BOM line. All ranked candidate parts are shown with pricing, stock, and distributor info. Click swap on any alternative and confirm — the substitution is recorded with timestamp and reason."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Can I see substitution history?"
					answer="Yes. Each BOM line has a collapsible substitution timeline showing all swaps with the old MPN, new MPN, timestamp, and trigger reason. Full audit trail for compliance."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What is part ranking?"
					answer="When multiple alternatives exist, BOMexplorer ranks them by suitability. AI-suggested candidates are marked with a badge. Rank 2+ results are automatically stored as alternatives for future reference."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Export</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="What export formats are supported?"
					answer="Free tier: CSV export. Pro tier: CSV and XLSX (Excel format) export."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Will locked parts survive re-export?"
					answer="Yes. Locked parts are preserved across re-matching and re-export. Use row locking to freeze confirmed parts so they never change unexpectedly."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Billing & plans</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="Is there a free tier?"
					answer="Yes, always free. Includes 3 projects, 50 parts per project, 3 providers (OEMSecrets, DigiKey, Mouser), 50 AI Assist lines/month, 5 AI Explainer invocations/month, CSV export, natural language BOM filtering, manual search, lock/unlock BOM lines, DNP marking, price monitoring (nightly alerts), project cloning, and part alternatives + substitution history. No credit card required."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What does Pro include?"
					answer="Unlimited projects, unlimited parts per project, all 5 providers (adds Nexar premium and FindChips premium), 500 AI Assist lines/month, 20 AI Explainer invocations/month, XLSX export (Excel format), and all free plan features. $10/month via Paddle."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What are Token Packs?"
					answer="Token packs are add-ons purchasable via Paddle when your AI quotas are exhausted. Tokens do not expire monthly. Starter pack: 100 tokens at $5 USD with 180-day expiry. Additional packs may be configured. Available on any plan."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Is there a free trial of Pro?"
					answer="Yes, a 60-day Pro trial is available. Provisioned via internal webhook (e.g. course enrollment). You get full Pro plan access for 60 days. After expiry, your account reverts to free plan limits. This is a one-time offer and cannot be re-provisioned."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How is payment processed?"
					answer="All Pro subscriptions and token packs are processed securely through Paddle. Supports cards, Apple Pay, and more. Cancel anytime from preferences — access continues until billing period ends."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Do you offer discounts?"
					answer="Contact us for academic and open-source project discounts. We support educators and community builders with special pricing."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How do locked lines work?"
					answer="Selecting or swapping a part auto-locks if the preference is enabled. Locked lines prevent accidental changes during re-matching operations."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="What happens after trial expiry?"
					answer="Even if the plan field remains 'paid', expired trial users get free-tier limits enforced. Per-user overrides can be set by admins via max_projects_override and max_parts_per_project_override."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Preferences & configuration</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="What can I configure in preferences?"
					answer="Global preferences: distributor order, excluded distributors, preferred manufacturers, accept generic passives, lifecycle policy, currency, region, grade. Per-project overrides: distributor restrictions, quantity, grade, lifecycle policy (null values inherit from global)."
				/>

				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6 mt-12 font-mono pl-4 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-secondary)]">Privacy & data</h2>

				<FaqItem
					question="Do you store my BOM data?"
					answer="Your BOM files are processed in real-time. Raw CSV rows are preserved as JSON per line to enable re-matching without re-import. Create an account to save projects permanently. We only retain the minimum data necessary for providing the service."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="Is my component data shared with providers?"
					answer="No. We query providers' public APIs and websites but never share your BOM data with them. Your component lists remain private."
				/>

				<FaqItem
					question="How do you handle data security?"
					answer="JWT authentication with short-lived access + refresh tokens in httpOnly cookies. All data is encrypted in transit and at rest. Password reset uses tokenised email links with 24h expiry and always-200 responses to prevent email enumeration."
				/>
			</div>

			<div class="mt-16 text-center">
				<p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-4">
					Still have questions?
				</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-md font-semibold hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-blue-500/40 transition-all duration-200 inline-block">
					Contact Us
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</MarketingLayout>